{
  "sn": "Journey to Haven",
  "plot": "DEV: Rance confirmed Karsite involvement—red robes, prisoner-taking suggests ritual sacrifice/blood magic revival. Collapsed from Gift-shock; Senta carried him unconscious for 4 days to Haven. Arrived at Healers' Collegium; Rolan (Queen's Own Companion) greeted them. PEND: Rance's memories need retrieval (Mind-Healer required). Gift identification and training urgently needed. Karsite prisoner-taking motives unknown.",
  "entities": [
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Rance",
      "c": "Gift-shock coma for 4 days during transit; stabilized by herbs but channels remain fragile. Committed to contingency: demands knockout if he loses control to prevent harming leadership. Currently unconscious in Healers' Collegium.",
      "k": ["Rance"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Senta",
      "c": "STANCE-Rance: bond deepening—protective, affectionate ('you are mine as you are mine'); impressed by his strategic thinking and caution regarding regicide risk; refuses separation even after exhaustion from 4-day forced march. IDENTITY: Record-speed journey to Haven (4 days); supernatural endurance demonstrated. Speculation confirmed to self: Rance's Gift likely unprecedented, untrainable—worse than Firestarting, not seen in 5 centuries.",
      "k": ["Senta"]
    },
    {
      "t": "character",
      "n": "Rolan",
      "c": "Queen's Own Companion. Met Senta at Collegium gates; offered support and reassurance.",
      "k": ["Rolan", "Queen's Own"]
    },
    {
      "t": "lore",
      "n": "Karsite Blood Magic",
      "c": "Rance theorizes prisoner-taking relates to ritual sacrifice, demon summoning—practices officially banned in Karse for decades but potentially revived. Red-robed attackers obscured Karsite features to implicate Menmellith. Senta confirms: 'Fires of Vkandis Sunlord' consumed 'impure souls' for centuries; stories hold more truth than Valdemarans know.",
      "k": ["Karsite Blood Magic", "Karse", "Vkandis Sunlord"]
    }
  ]
}
